════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Growing suburb with strong family appeal.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Mount Gravatt East continues to attract families and first-home buyers drawn to its relative affordability, good schools and strong community feel. Improving amenity and proximity to Westfield Garden City make it an increasingly popular choice.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the buyer profile active in Mount Gravatt East and what they prioritise. I use that knowledge to position your property precisely and build campaigns that attract motivated buyers.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The local shopping strip on Newnham Road gives Mount Gravatt East a genuine village feel that is increasingly valued by families who want walkable everyday convenience without paying inner-city prices. The surrounding parklands and bushland reserves along the escarpment provide a natural backdrop that is hard to find in an established suburb this close to the CBD. The suburb's quieter character compared with busier Mount Gravatt to the west has attracted a loyal owner-occupier base who tend to hold long, keeping stock levels tight and supporting vendor prices. Buyers from the Coorparoo and Greenslopes markets who want more land and space have been driving demand in Mount Gravatt East over recent years.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Mount Gravatt East Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Southern Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Growing Suburb</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Strong family demand</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/mount-gravatt" style="color:#c4912a;">Mount Gravatt</a>, <a href="/suburbs/upper-mount-gravatt" style="color:#c4912a;">Upper Mount Gravatt</a>, <a href="/suburbs/coorparoo" style="color:#c4912a;">Coorparoo</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

